cat > ~/api_audit.log <<'EOF'
================================================
SESSION 27: API BUSINESS LOGIC AUDIT LOG
================================================

1. BOLA / IDOR PROFILE TEST

Original Request:
GET /api/v1/profile/101

Modified Request:
GET /api/v1/profile/102

Result:
Changing the profile ID from 101 to 102 allowed access to the private CISO profile.

Leaked CISO Secret:
TITAN_MASTER_KEY_2026

Remediation:
The API should enforce object-level authorization on the server side. A user should only be allowed to access profile data that belongs to their own account. Changing an ID in the URL should not allow access to another user's private profile.


2. DISCOUNT CODE BUSINESS LOGIC TEST

Original Checkout Request:
POST /api/v1/checkout

Original Body:
{"discount_code":"0000"}

Payload Range Tested:
9900 to 9999

Winning Discount Code:
9912

Successful Response:
{"discount":"100% OFF","status":"Success","total":"$0.00"}

Result:
The hidden discount code 9912 was discovered. When this code was submitted to the checkout API, the response changed to 100% OFF and the total became $0.00.

Remediation:
The application should not rely on hidden or guessable discount codes. Discount codes should be random, rate-limited, tied to specific users, expire after use, and protected from brute-force attempts.
EOF
